							<h3>Title: The Complete Works</h3>
							<h5>Author: Charles Dickens</h5>
							<p>Book Description: Signed copy. London: Briggs and Blower, 1874-76., 1874. The Royal Literature Edition. Ten complete volumes. Vintage binding of luxuriant green with 
							gilt titles, and gilt embossing of the spines; superbly marbled end pages and edges. Includes original  illustrations Greg, Smyth, Arnold, etc. Dickens signature on first 
							inner page. A  well-preserved set, which represents a unique moment in history. Expected annual increase in value of 6.9%.  </p>
						</div>
